            <notesStmt>
                <note type="title" date-time="2023-04-21T16:18:52.018Z" user="john">Although appearing as a single text in all Kangyurs, the Degé dkar chag notes that it is divided into two main sections of which this is the first, the “root tantra.” The second main section is the “subsequent tantra,” see next text Toh 724a. Note that the Tōhoku Catalog assigns the number 724 to both parts.</note>
                <note type="title" date-time="2023-04-21T16:18:52.018Z" user="john">The Degé dkar chag notes: “sgrol ma ral pa gyen brdzes rtsa ba’i rtog pa las lhag par mos pa’i phreng ba zhes bya ba’i rig pa’i rgyal po rdzogs so yan cad bzhugs so,” the point in the text mentioned as the end of this first section being on folio 16a of volume tsha.</note>
            </notesStmt>
